#!CNavyBlue #!N  #!Rcolmape Using the Colormap Editor 
#!N #!EC #!N #!N The Colormap Editor is a window that 
enables you to map colors to specified data values, the results 
of which are displayed in the visual image. In addition to 
color, the Colormap Editor also controls the mapping of  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   opacity 
#!EF to data, which is the degree of the image's transparency 
in relation to its background. Maximum opacity shows the color calculated 
by the hue, saturation, and value fields; minimum opacity calculates colors 
so that the image is faintly visible in front of the 
background. In summary, the Colormap Editor enables you to: #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o Control the range of 
data values over which the mapping occurs. #!N #!I30 #!N o 
Select the colors that are mapped to the range of values. 
#!N #!I30 #!N o Select the opacities that are mapped to 
the range of values. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N When the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Colormap #!EF stand-in from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Special #!EF category is 
connected to the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Color #!EF tool as shown in the 
visual program fragment in  #!Lcmap175,dxall365 f Figure 75  #!EL  , the combination can be used 
in place of the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoColor #!EF tool. #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   
 #!Rcmap175 #!N #!N Graphics omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the 
manual. #!N Figure 75. Fragment of Visual Program Using Colormap #!EF 
#!N #!EC #!N #!N To use the Colormap Editor: #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Double-click on the Colormap 
tool in the VPE window or select either the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Open 
Selected Colormap Editors #!EF option from the VPE or the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Open All Colormap Editors #!EF from the Image window  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Windows 
#!EF menu. #!N Note: From the VPE, this option is  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Open Colormap Editor #!EF . For this option to be available, 
the Colormap icon must be selected. #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 2. 
The Colormap Editor appears. Make necessary adjustments to values, as described 
in  #!Lentv,dxall366 h Entering Values in a Colormap Editor  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N  #!Lcoled76,dxall365 f Figure 76  #!EL  
illustrates the organization of the Colormap Editor window. #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   
 #!Rcoled76 #!N #!N Graphics omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the 
manual. #!N Figure 76. Colormap Editor #!EF #!N #!EC #!N #!N 
